==English==
===Etymology===
Often thought to be a contraction of the title ''Dar''k Lord of the Si''th''. ''Darth'' may also be a [[portmanteau]] of ''[[dark]]'' and ''[[death]]''.

===Noun===
'''Darth'''

#(''Star Wars''). The title preceding the name of a [[Sith]] Lord, referring to Star Wars villains.
#A Sith Lord.

===Adjective===

#  To be frighteningly evil, or directly responsible for distinctly negative events
#: Because of their bosses lack of respect for them, the employees referred to him as "Darth Phil."

